### ğŸ’¬ Modern Terminal UI with Progressive Streaming

**Built with Textual framework** for a responsive, beautiful CLI experience:

- âœ… **Progressive streaming**: Watch sub-agent tool calls appear in real-time
- âœ… **Real-time reasoning**: See agents think and make decisions live
- âœ… **ESC cancellation**: Cancel long-running operations anytime (NEW in v0.1.38)
- âœ… **Non-blocking execution**: Scroll and interact while agents work
- âœ… **Smart input management**: Auto-disabled during processing (no duplicate queries)
- âœ… **Tool execution tracking**: See exactly which data sources agents are calling
- âœ… **Multi-agent progress**: Visual workflow transitions with status updates
- âœ… **Markdown rendering**: Tables, code blocks, syntax highlighting
- âœ… **Auto-save reports**: All responses >200 chars saved to `reports/` directory
- âœ… **Keyboard shortcuts**: `ESC` (cancel), `Ctrl+C` (clear), `Ctrl+Q` (quit)

### âš¡ Smart API Caching (NEW in v0.1.41)

**DuckDB-powered caching layer** that dramatically reduces API calls and improves performance:

- âœ… **42 cached tools** across 9 data sources (Yahoo, SEC, FRED, Treasury, Tiingo, Finnhub, etc.)
- âœ… **Intelligent TTL**: Real-time (60s), fundamentals (1h), economic data (24h) expiration
- âœ… **Cache warming**: Pre-populate with `/cache warm` (23 common queries: FAANG+ stocks, indices, GDP/CPI)
- âœ… **Performance stats**: `/cache` shows hit rates, cache size, API savings by tool
- âœ… **Manual control**: `/cache clear` to invalidate all entries
- âœ… **Color-coded metrics**: Green (â‰¥75% hit rate), yellow (â‰¥50%), red (<50%)
- âœ… **SHA256 keys**: Unique cache keys from function arguments
- âœ… **Persistent storage**: `~/.navam-invest/cache/api_cache.duckdb`
- âœ… **Zero configuration**: Works out-of-the-box, automatic cleanup

**Expected Performance**:
- 20-40% hit rates on economic indicators (FRED)
- 40-70% hit rates on treasury data (yield curves)
- 10-30% hit rates on equity data (depends on symbols queried)
- Higher rates over time as you query the same stocks repeatedly

